    message: Non-UTF-8 file content behavior unspecified; treated as I/O error via read-to-string.
    reasoning: Prompt says "read the current content off disk (propagating any I/O error as its display string)" and then hashes it as a `&str`. That forces `read_to_string`, which fails on invalid UTF-8 with an InvalidData error whose display string is propagated. Prompt never says whether that is intended or whether such a file should count as drifted.
